Tuesday Night, August 4th the ENP & HR School Boards unanimously approved the South Hardin Schools Return to Learn & Reopening Plan. Please read the finalized version of the plan at the linked website below.

On Friday, August 7th at 4 PM the Registration Process will begin for the 2020-21 School Year. Information on how to register will be sent soon.

The first question on your registration document will ask if you plan to attend in-person or participate in our 100% online learning program for the first semester. Please read the descriptions of each of those options, and the entire plan when making the decision that is best for your family for the 2020-21 School Year. Please reach out to Dr. Zellmer or any building principal with questions about the plan.

https://sites.google.com/view/shreturntolearn/home

post_text:
The Iowa Department of Human Services will distribute additional food assistance benefits to families throughout the state.

The Families First CoronaVirus Act allows states to issue benefits to households with children in prekindergarten through 12th grade that lost access to free and reduced-price school meals due to extended school closures last spring.

Eligible families will receive $307.80 per child. If your household received food assistance benefits in April, May or June, you will see that amount added to your EBT card by July 15. If you have not received food benefits in the past three months, you will get a P-EBT card in the mail before July 21.

The P-EBT cards will come in a white envelope addressed with your child's name, with a return address from Austin, TX. The cards themselves will be white with black font, with "IOWA P-EBT" printed at the top. Once you receive your card, follow the included instructions to activate it.

Learn more: https://dhs.iowa.gov/P-EBT

post_text: Weekly Press Release: April 20, 2020 with updated information about the school closure.
text: Weekly Press Release: April 20, 2020 with updated information about the school closure.

post_text: Governor Reynolds announced this morning that schools will remain closed for the remainder of the 2019-20 School Year and Spring Sports Seasons have been cancelled. Now many more unprecedented and challenging decisions will have to be made in the days and weeks ahead by school districts throughout the state. Please be patient as we now begin to process what this means for us at South Hardin Schools. What I can guarantee you is that educational learning opportunities and our food distribution program will continue through the end of our scheduled school year. We will find a way to celebrate and honor our Class of 2020, and to honor those staff members who won't be with us next year. We will get through this! Remember we are #StrongerTogether! Dr. Z. will provide more information on Monday afternoon with his weekly video press release.

Governor Reynolds has required schools to be closed through April 30th, an additional 14 school days beyond the original 4 week closure. The Emergency Food Program will continue through April 30th to support #OurKids and #OurFamilies.
Schools buildings will remain closed and we will also be closing all school playgrounds to help slow the spread of COVID-19 through April 30th, except for staff needing to perform essential functions. Please help us partner to stop the spread!
More information will be provided early next week on how we will address the new educational requirements coming down from the state at our local district level.
Dr. Z.

post_text:
This evening the Governor of Iowa recommended all schools in the state close for a period of 4 weeks. We are currently on break at South Hardin Schools on spring break. We will make decisions on the long-term recommendation in the days ahead following press conference and action taken by legislators. Effective immediately, all buildings are closed and all activities are cancelled at the request of Governor Reynolds. This includes any open gym, athletic practice, rehearsal, or any other activity otherwise sanctioned or not by the school district. Facilities will be accessible only to those personnel essential for continuity of operations including administrators, clerical staff, custodians, maintenance staff, and contractors.

This is a very dynamic and fluid situation and more information will be forthcoming as available.

Dr. Z.

Immediate Job Opening in the ENP School District:
Bus Aide for a bus that transports 2 students to Cedar Falls each day. Approximate hours are 7:15am-9:45am and 1:45pm-4:15pm. Hourly pay is $9.51 per hour, and follows a regular school calendar. This is a great opportunity for a stay at home parent or retired person to be out and about and add to their income! Please call Nancy Webb at the ENP District Office at 641-939-5631 with questions or inquiries.

post_text: October is National Principal Appreciation Month! At South Hardin Schools we are blessed with four great building leaders who work countless hours, deal with challenging situations, and strive to support #OurStaff in providing #OurKids with top notch educational experiences in #OurSchools. Thanks to Mr. Henrichs (ENP Elementary Principal), Mr. Mangold (HR Elementary Principal, Ms. Nachazel (SH Middle School Principal), & Mr. Rundall (SH High School Principal) for helping our schools embrace today's challenges and prepare for tomorrow's world! Please take time this month to reach out and show your appreciation for their hard work and dedication to South Hardin Schools!

post_text: Immediate Job Opening: The Hubbard-Radcliffe School District has an immediate opening for a kitchen team member at the South Hardin Middle School in Hubbard. Roughly 6 hours per day, beginning at 7:00am, Monday through Friday, following the school calendar. This is a great opportunity for a stay at home parent or retired person to be out and about and add to their income! Candidate must be able to stand for extended periods of time, lift up to 40 pounds, and have basic kitchen skills. Must be able to pass background check. Please stop by the administration office of the school for an application or email cgiguere@southhardin.org with questions or interest.
